100 Years Ago Today, This is What Was Happening ...

On October 25, 1925, the League of Nations convened in Geneva, focusing on disarmament and international peace efforts amid rising tensions in Europe. In the United States, the ongoing Scopes Trial drew national attention, highlighting the clash between modern science and traditional beliefs in education. Meanwhile, economic concerns continued to loom as the world grappled with the aftereffects of the post-World War I era.
